casebody.data:
Kirkland, Respondent, v. Dyer, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 12, 1892.) Action by Thomas Kirkland against James Dyer.

Argued before Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

Ho opinion. Motion for leave to appeal to the court of appeals denied, with $10 costs. For decision on appeal, see 19 N. Y. Supp. 1011.
